Key Match Events: Royce Lewis nearly had his sixth career grand slam for Minnesota in the seventh inning, as his drive to left field was initially called a home run but a review showed that the ball hit off the top of the wall and back into play for a two-run double.
Matt Wallner homered for the second straight game.
Brooks Lee snapped an 0-for-19 stretch with a go-ahead, two-run double.
Post-Match Reflections: ‘We got some really nice swings,’ Minnesota manager Rocco Baldelli said. ‘You could feel the offense kind of brewing there.... You could feel the guys, the good energy, the good at-bats that they gave us. They were really locked in and doing their part in a nice way.’
